title: Sadyr Japarov
added: Japarov is accused of adherence to Kyrgyz nationalism, with many labelling him as "a staunch nationalist inclined to violence", and an anti-Uzbek.<ref name="автоссылка2">{{cite web|url=https://kloop.kg/blog/2020/10/07/pochemu-osuzhdennogo-sadyra-zhaparova-tak-prodvigayut-v-premer-ministry-i-kak-on-stal-tak-populyaren-sredi-nekotoryh-protestuyushhih/|title=Почему осужденного Садыра Жапарова так продвигают в премьер-министры и как он стал так популярен среди некоторых протестующих|publisher=Kloop.kg|accessdate=2020-11-24}}</ref> It is noted that during the time of Japarov's work anti-corruption departments, he "did not show significant success in the fight against corruption", being accused of having connections with the "thief in law" and a northern crime boss, Kamchy Kolbaev.<ref name="автоссылка2" />

title: Sadyr Japarov
added: Japarov first five executive orders were related to spiritual development, a new personnel policy, business protection, migration, and mining.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Spiritual development, new personnel policy, business protection, migration, mining: Japarov signs 5 first executive orders|url=https://m.akipress.com/news:653927:Spiritual_development,_new_personnel_policy,_business_protection,_migration,_mining__Japarov_signs_5_first_executive_orders/|access-date=2021-01-29|website=m.akipress.com}}</ref>
